# Brownies

Based on [https://tasty.co/recipe/…](https://tasty.co/recipe/the-best-one-bowl-brownies) ([wayback](http://web.archive.org/web/20251122165149/https://tasty.co/recipe/the-best-one-bowl-brownies))

{ rating="4" image="brownies.jpeg" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

- [ ] 1 cup unsalted butter, 2 sticks
- [ ] 4 oz semi-sweet chocolate bar, coarsely chopped
- [ ] 1.5 cups granulated sugar
- [ ] 3/4 cup brown sugar
- [ ] 1 Tbsp vanilla extract
- [ ] 1 tsp espresso powder
- [ ] 1 tsp salt
- [ ] 3 large eggs
- [ ] 1 cup all-purpose flour
- [ ] 2/3 cup Dutch-process cocoa powder
- [ ] 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips
- [ ] Nonstick cooking spray

## Recipe

1. Preheat the oven to 350F
1. Add the butter and chopped chocolate bar to a large microwave-safe bowl. Microwave in 15-second increments, stirring between each, until smooth. Let sit for 3 minutes to cool slightly
1. Add the granulated and brown sugars, vanilla, espresso powder, and salt. Whisk to combine
1. Whisk in the eggs one at a time until fully combined and glossy
1. Sift the flour and cocoa powder into the bowl and fold in with a spatula until just combined. Fold in the chocolate chips
1. Grease a 9-inch square baking pan. Spread the batter evenly in the pan
1. Bake for 35-40 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out with a few moist crumbs attached
1. Let cool completely before cutting

## Notes

- For fudgier texture and shiny crust: heat butter and sugar together to 110-120F before mixing with eggs (technique from [King Arthur Baking](https://www.kingarthurbaking.com/recipes/fudge-brownies-recipe) ([wayback](http://web.archive.org/web/20260115000000*/https://www.kingarthurbaking.com/recipes/fudge-brownies-recipe)))
